00:26:34.310 --> 00:26:37.730
The polarization is generated
by a process known as Thomson

00:26:37.730 --> 00:26:41.800
scattering-- scattering of
photons off free electrons.

00:26:41.800 --> 00:26:44.570
So the photons scatter
off free electrons,

00:26:44.570 --> 00:26:48.560
and each electron,
along the line of sight,

00:26:48.560 --> 00:26:54.800
sees a local temperature
quadruple-- a local temperature

00:26:54.800 --> 00:26:58.970
